<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="terror-n">terror <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'terə(r)/    美 /'terər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u-a-feeling-of-extreme-fear">1.★ <strong>[U] 惊恐；恐惧 a feeling of extreme fear；恐怖 (行动)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>flee in terror</strong>
仓皇逃走</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The student was <strong>in terror of</strong> the teacher, who had always been hard on him.
那个学生对老师怕得要命，老师一贯对他很严厉。</p></div>

<h4 id="2c">2.<strong>[C] 引起恐怖的人 / 物：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These street gangs have become the terror of the neighbourhood.
这些街头团伙使得周围邻居谈之色变。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>terrorism /'terərɪzəm/ n <br />
terrorist /'terərɪst/ n   </p></div>